### [2 Kings (2 Samuel) Chapter 5](../../../bib/kjv/sa2005.htm#001.md)

[2 Kings (2 Samuel)](../../../bib/kjv/sa2001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">sa2 5:0</span></span>

Overview

[Sa2 5:1](../../../bib/kjv/sa2005.htm#001.md), The tribes come to Hebron
and anoint David over Israel; [Sa2
5:4](../../../bib/kjv/sa2005.htm#004.md), David's age; [Sa2
5:6](../../../bib/kjv/sa2005.htm#006.md), He taking Zion from the
Jebusites, dwells in it; [Sa2 5:11](../../../bib/kjv/sa2005.htm#011.md),
Hiram sends to David; [Sa2 5:13](../../../bib/kjv/sa2005.htm#013.md),
Eleven sons are born to him in Jerusalem; [Sa2
5:17](../../../bib/kjv/sa2005.htm#017.md), David, directed by God, smites
the Philistines at Baal-perazim; [Sa2
5:22](../../../bib/kjv/sa2005.htm#022.md), and again at the mulberry trees.

